'''Michael ("Mike") Sylvester''' (born December 10, 1951 in [[Cincinnati]], [[Ohio]]) is a [[basketball]] coach at [[Cincinnati Hills Christian Academy]] and former Olympian.

==Biography==
Sylvester graduated from [[Moeller High School]] and played [[college basketball]] at the [[University of Dayton]].  He was drafted with the 15th pick in the sixth round by the [[Detroit Pistons]] in the [[1974 NBA Draft]] and won the silver medal on the [[Italy national basketball team|Italian team]] at the [[1980 Summer Olympics]] in [[Moscow]]. Sylvester is a current resident of [[Loveland, Ohio]].<ref name="Herald Meale">{{cite news|title=CHCA lands former pro, Olympian|author=Tony Meale|first=Tony|last=Meale|work=The Loveland Herald|publisher=The Community Press|date=2009-07-01|accessdate=2009-07-02|url=http://communitypress.cincinnati.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/C2/20090701/SPT01/907010359/|quote=Sylvester, who had dual citizenship in Italy and the United States, also helped the Italian team to a silver medal at the 1980 Olympics in Moscow .... Born in the [[Elder High School|Elder]] heartland, the current Loveland resident is eager to begin his tenure at [[Cincinnati Hills Christian Academy|CHCA]].}}</ref> A 6'5" extremely accurate shooter, Throughout his career in Italy (1977-1990) he played for [[Olimpia Milano]], [[Scavolini Pesaro]], [[Basket Rimini]] and [[Virtus Bologna]].<ref name="Mike">[http://195.56.77.208/player/?id=SIL-MIK Mike Silvester] {{it icon}}</ref>

